SYNOPSIS
        void tell_visible(object oRoom, string sMsg, mixed xExclude,
			  object oVisCheck)

DESCRIPTION
	Sends the message '<sMsg>' to all living objects in object '<oRoom>'
	that are visible to object '<oVisCheck>' except for objects
	'<xExclude>', which can be either an object or an array of objects.

	If the function 'catch_tell' is defines in the objects this message goes
	to, then it will be called with '<sMsg>' as the argument.

EXAMPLE
	// This first example will tell all living objects visible to
	// this_player() in the room the message supplied.
	tell_visible(environment(this_player()), "I can see you!\n",
		     0, this_player());

